 1990-26631990-12-060OLD INAC,  ,  ,  , 
PrecisAuthority: (a) to accept the transfer from the Province of Alberta of the administration and control over approximately 16,000 acres of land situate in the areas of Goose Lake and Sturgeon Lake, mineral rights included with some tracts as well as with some others already in the possession of the STURGEON LAKE BAND OF INDIANS; and (b) to set those lands and mineral rights apart for the use and benefit of that band as additions to their reserves No. 154 and No. 154A.
